rComments: I met my goal of developing verbal and written communication skills thanks to Prof Kahramans guidance and quality of instruction. She was passionate about the course material and demonstrated a sincere commitment to her students throughout the course. If youre interested in learning Turkish, this course and professor are the right place to start!

I took a full-year course with Professor Kahraman, and I enjoyed the course a lot. She cares a lot about her students and is available at flexible times outside class for those needing extra help. Attendance and participation is key for her and she expects you to do the work. If do your homework and participate, a good grade is guaranteed.

Not gunna lie- taking a language class at the university level is tough. It becomes more manageable when you have a professor like Nefise Kahraman. You can tell she really cares about the students success and is willing to go above and beyond to help you succeed. Do the work and seek help if you need it and youll enjoy class with prof Kahraman!

Professor Kahraman is a really passionate professor who deeply cares about the content she is teaching as well as the academic success of her students. Although attendance is mandatory, she is extremely understanding when it comes to missing class (within reason) and was both personal and professional in all interactions with students.

If you need an easy 100 grade take it (its a guarantee, I easily got a 95), but be prepared she is totally unprofessional. I didn't learn anything new. She picked fights with students sitting at back (native speakers) and was always yelling at them.
